BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 611 Tm (1. GOVERNANCE OBJECTIVE) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 590 Tm (The governance structure of Aura exists to preserve structural integrity of discourse.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 569 Tm (Moderation is not editorial authority. Moderation exists to protect factual continuity,) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 555 Tm (prevent direct harm, preserve identity-bound accountability, and maintain record stability.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 534 Tm (Disagreement, criticism, and institutional challenge are not grounds for intervention.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 499 Tm (2. MODERATION AUTHORITY) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 478 Tm (Aura moderation is centralized. Moderators act as structural custodians rather than content) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 464 Tm (editors.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 443 Tm (Moderators do not promote, rank, or suppress ideas. Their role is limited to preserving) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 429 Tm (structural integrity.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 394 Tm (3. CONDITIONS FOR MODERATION ACTION) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 373 Tm (Moderation may intervene only under: verified factual distortion, direct harassment or) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 359 Tm (targeted personal harm, impersonation or identity manipulation, illegal material, spam or) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 345 Tm (automated distortion of discourse.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 324 Tm (Moderation does not intervene for: political disagreement, institutional criticism,) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 310 Tm (controversial opinions, unpopular viewpoints, satire or rhetorical expression.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 275 Tm (4. MODERATION PROCESS) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 254 Tm (Step 1 - Identification: content enters moderation through user reports, AI-assisted) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 240 Tm (flagging, or manual review. AI signals initiate review but do not trigger automatic removal.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 219 Tm (Step 2 - Verification: moderators verify whether structural rules have been violated.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 198 Tm (Step 3 - Action: removal of content, request for revision, temporary restriction, or account) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 184 Tm (review.) Tj T* ET
